We score each candidate head by feeding the concatenation of the output bi-LSTM vectors for the head hk, the preposition p and the direct dependent d through an MLP, with a fully connected tanh layer to obtain a non-linear projection of the concatenation, followed by a fully-connected softmax layer:
p(hkis head) = MLPattach([lstm out(hk);
lstm out(p);
lstm out(d)]) (3)
To train the model, we use cross-entropy loss at the output layer for each candidate head in the
training set.
